Web Accessibility (a11y) means ensuring your products are fully usable by everyone, including people with visual, cognitive, or physical limitations. The W3C establishes the WCAG guidelines to standardize accessibility:

1. Contrast Ratios: Ensure all regular texts maintain a contrast ratio of at least 4.5:1 against the background.
2. Keyboard Traversal: All buttons and inputs must be fully accessible using 'Tab' and 'Enter' keys, with clear outline focus rings:

```css
/* Focus states are critical for keyboard-navigable access */
button:focus-visible,
input:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid #6366f1;
  outline-offset: 4px;
}
```

3. Semantic Outline: Screen readers navigate pages by jumping across headers. Every page MUST have a single <h1> tag, followed by nested, logical <h2> and <h3> tags. Never skip a heading level.
